<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54368" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.theintrinsicperspective.com/p/they-die-every-day" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“They die every day”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; if you like Terry Bisson&#8217;s &#8220;They&#8217;re Made Out of Meat&#8221; (<a href="https://jerrywbrown.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/They-are-made-out-of-meat-Bisson-Terry.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener">here</a>), you&#8217;ll like this dialogue by Erik Hoel</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54364" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bronx-socrates-a-stand-up-intellectual-302505358.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Real teaching is about genuinely connecting with your students as people. They don’t care how much you know unless they know how much you care”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; “Bronx Socrates,” a documentary about revered philosophy teacher Bob Gurland, premieres this month. </span><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54367" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zcz1IjShtzI" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Here’s the trailer</a></span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54362" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://musgrave.substack.com/p/at-the-coalface" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Academics, when someone asks you how things are going, you can send them this</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Paul Musgrave summarizes the various problems facing academia right now and why &#8220;the vibes are very bad&#8221;</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54350" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://aeon.co/essays/why-medically-assisted-dying-should-be-legalised" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“The question… is about how to make progress in a debate where both sides are both deeply dug in and all too predictable”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Michael Cholbi on the disputes over assisted dying and the concept of freedom over death</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54348" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://social-epistemology.com/2025/07/14/dogwhistles-figleaves-and-slogans-in-the-second-trump-term-jennifer-saul/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">“Dogwhistles are likely to become very important in an America where expression has become so restricted”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Jennifer Saul applies ideas from her book on strategic and manipulative language to recent events</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54344" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zpAeygE4d1A" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Are photos taken or discovered?</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; a video essay on what they could, but don&#8217;t, call &#8220;digital photo modal realism&#8221; (via MeFi)</span></li>
<li class="wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><span class="heap-of-link_name wp-dark-mode-bg-image"><a id="link-54341" class="track_this_link wp-dark-mode-bg-image" href="https://ksetiya.substack.com/p/horse-whispering" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">We typically hold that definitions cannot be circular, but “McDowell rejects that constraint and thus the substantive project of philosophical analysis, understood in metaphysical terms”</a></span> <span class="heap-of-link_description wp-dark-mode-bg-image">&#8212; Kieran Setiya on McDowell&#8217;s quietism </span></li>
